==English==
===Etymology===
Contracted from Middle English ''[[hem]]'', him

===Pronunciation===
əm, /əm/, /@m/

===Pronoun===
'''’em'''

#(''informal'') Contraction of '''[[them]]'''.
#:''Give ’em what they want.''

====Usage notes====
*'''’Em''' is commonly used to replace '''them''' but can also be used to replace "him".
